criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion criteria:

          1. post bronchodilator forced expiratory volume in 1 s [FEV1]/forced vital capacity [FVC]
             ,70% and FEV1 ,50% of the predicted value);

          2. bronchial dilation test (BDT) negative.

        Exclusion criteria:

          1. acute exacerbation in the previous 4 weeks;

          2. use of oral corticosteroids within 4 weeks;

          3. smoking more than 10 cigarettes daily;

          4. history of other respiratory, cardiovascular, neuromuscular, and musculoskeletal
             diseases that could interfere with the exercise performance and inspiratory muscle
             activities.
